\begin_layout Standard
The infinite binary tree is self-similar, in that one can look at the subtree
 lying under any given node, and see that is isomorphic to the tree as a
 whole.
 A given subtree is easily and uniquely located: one may take a walk down
 the tree, taking either the left 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 or the right 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

