\begin_layout Standard
The matrix given above is unimodular: that is, its determinant is one.
 This can be easily seen because the determinant of 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 is one, and the determinant of a product of matrices is equal to the product
 of the determinants.
 The entries of the matrix are always integers, and thus its easily seen
