 lead to divergence upon iteration.
 To get absolute convergence, one wants the final form of the affine matrix
 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{x}=d_{b_{1}}\circ d_{b_{2}}\circ\cdots$
\end_inset

 to be 
\begin_inset Formula \[
d_{x}=\left(\begin{array}{ccc}
1\; & 0\; & 0\\
u & 0 & 0\\
v & 0 & 0\end{array}\right)\]

\end_inset

 so that the fixed point is 
\begin_inset Formula $(u,v)$
\end_inset

